<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,1549,1897]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1801,1825]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kemp" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[322,509,1801,1825]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Ilyoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stevensi">
<emphasis box="[322,509,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Ilyoplax stevensi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed along the eastern (Iranian) coast and northern (
<collectingCountry box="[1274,1361,1801,1825]" name="Kuwait" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
) coast of the Persian Gulf, while missing in its southern part. Its only congener in the Persian Gulf, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kemp" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1348,1436,1837,1861]" class="Malacostraca" family="Dotillidae" genus="Ilyoplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frater">
<emphasis box="[1348,1357,1838,1861]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1372,1436,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">frater</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded from the all Gulf states coasts except the Iraqi coast, which is mainly due to lack of sampling.
</paragraph>
